e an AI agent task with Telegram for your team for Lead Bots — run completed at {{ $now.toFormat('HH:mm') }}","otherOptions":{}},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.slack","typeVersion":2.3,"position":[5481,400],"id":"47cdf41f-1b33-4161-932e-1796e32bef49","name":"Send Summary to Slack","retryOnFail":true,"maxTries":3,"waitBetweenTries":2000,"onError":"continueErrorOutput"},{"parameters":{"assignments":{"assignments":[{"id":"1aa7a4e9-f63d-4f27-927b-a5a3bf904370","name":"failedNode","value":"={{ $json.error?.node?.name || 'unknown' }}","type":"string"},{"id":"3c54116a-a006-407e-9b43-0b97c58f5715","name":"errorMessage","value":"={{ $json.error?.message || JSON.stringify($json).slice(0,200) }}","type":"string"},{"id":"444cec2d-ce9f-4b23-bec2-5ff666e792b4","name":"workflow","value":"={{ $workflow.name }}","type":"string"}]},"options":{}},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.set","typeVersion":3.4,"position":[4833,1420],"id":"d4ce6a33-1957-437a-afed-53e5b5665c7c","name":"Capture Failure Context"},{"parameters":{"chatId":"={{ $json.chatId || 'OPS_CHAT_ID' }}","text":"=🚨 {{ $json.workflow }} failed at {{ $json.failedNode }}: {{ $json.errorMessage }}","additionalFields":{"appendAttribution":false}},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.telegram","typeVersion":1.2,"position":[5157,1420],"id":"79cf6672-3072-4384-9355-25cb98862928","name":"Escalate Failure to Telegram","retryOnFail":true,"maxTries":3,"waitBetweenTries":2000},{"parameters":{"content":"### Receive Inbound Webhook\n\nEntry point: listens for POST calls on `/wf07640-conversation`. Use the TEST url while building, switch callers to the PRODUCTION url after publishing.\n\nNext: Collect Raw Text","width":280,"height":232,"color":5},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[-330,520],"id":"39610f82-9324-1f7b-eebc-ca092fe5f7da","name":"Note: Receive Inbound Webhook"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Collect Raw Text\n\nShapes the item: writes `content`. Keeps the schema explicit between stages.\n\nNext: Extract Structured Fields","width":280,"height":232,"color":7},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[-6,520],"id":"5665569d-046e-8e74-0ae4-0713d4cb16a8","name":"Note: Collect Raw Text"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Extract Structured Fields\n\nPulls structured fields (sessionId, message, intent) out of free text using a strict extraction prompt.\n\nPorts: ①→ All Required Fields Found? · ②→ Capture Failure Context\n\n⚠ failures exit via the error rail","width":280,"height":232,"color":6},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[318,520],"id":"92c6a038-9000-69a7-404d-78161551f7b7","name":"Note: Extract Structured Fields"},{"parameters":{"content":"### OpenAI Chat Model\n\nChat model powering the AI step (model: `gpt-4o-mini`). Swap providers here without rewiring.\n\nFeeds **Extract Structured Fields** as `languageModel`\n\n🔑 OpenAI API key","width":280,"height":232,"color":6},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[561,1090],"id":"9211ca34-1a58-00d2-5e3e-039713aad54a","name":"Note: OpenAI Chat Model"},{"parameters":{"content":"### All Required Fields Found?\n\nTwo-way gate on `={{ $json.output?.sessionId }}`. TRUE continues the happy path, FALSE takes the alternate branch.\n\nPorts: ①→ Upsert into Google Sheets · ②→ Queue for Manual Review","width":280,"height":232,"color":2},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[885,520],"id":"61737faf-0e51-b7d6-bc0a-76ac26d4f03c","name":"Note: All Required Fields Found?"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Upsert into Google Sheets\n\ngoogleSheets — `appendOrUpdate` operation against the connected account.\n\nPorts: ①→ Merge Review Paths · ②→ Capture Failure Context\n\n↻ retries 3×/2s · ⚠ failures exit via the error rail · 🔑 Google OAuth2 / service account","width":280,"height":232,"color":2},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[1209,280],"id":"b74feaed-aac2-3391-5327-63a7479da755","name":"Note: Upsert into Google Sheets"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Queue for Manual Review\n\ntelegram — `action` operation against the connected account.\n\nPorts: ①→ Merge Review Paths · ②→ Capture Failure Context\n\n↻ retries 3×/2s · ⚠ failures exit via the error rail · 🔑 Telegram bot token","width":280,"height":232,"color":2},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[1533,880],"id":"27f34034-4112-b935-9a80-5cfb97b217cd","name":"Note: Queue for Manual Review"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Merge Review Paths\n\nRejoins 2 branches into one stream (mode: append) so downstream logic runs once.\n\nNext: Sort Conversations Newest First","width":280,"height":232,"color":7},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[2181,520],"id":"94bcc67a-03da-b7f9-a503-83944d1a52a3","name":"Note: Merge Review Paths"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Sort Conversations Newest First\n\nOrders items (newest first) so limits and digests pick the most relevant records.\n\nNext: Guard Non-Empty message","width":280,"height":232,"color":7},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[3153,520],"id":"653f90a3-ef5a-c9eb-1c53-68794c475e36","name":"Note: Sort Conversations Newest First"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Guard Non-Empty message\n\nDrops items that fail the condition; only qualifying items continue (no false branch).\n\nNext: Stamp Processing Time","width":280,"height":232,"color":7},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[3477,520],"id":"f1bec2d2-8d6a-1dac-fc08-3c08695c053d","name":"Note: Guard Non-Empty message"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Stamp Processing Time\n\nStamps `processedAt` with the current time for auditing.\n\nNext: Save Execution Metadata","width":280,"height":232,"color":7},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[3801,520],"id":"1a89c33e-5230-cdc5-e155-7d08174feb87","name":"Note: Stamp Processing Time"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Save Execution Metadata\n\nSaves key fields onto the execution record — searchable later in n8n's execution list.\n\nNext: Align Field Names","width":280,"height":232,"color":7},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[4125,520],"id":"f4b7dc81-78b1-5505-9b9c-7e6d1057f225","name":"Note: Save Execution Metadata"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Align Field Names\n\nNormalizes field names so every source feeds the same downstream schema.\n\nNext: Summarize Run Stats","width":280,"height":232,"color":7},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[4449,520],"id":"54d88ee2-42ff-a139-9148-6bf486534f6c","name":"Note: Align Field Names"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Summarize Run Stats\n\nShapes the item: writes `runAt`, `itemCount`, `status`. Keeps the schema explicit between stages.\n\nNext: Append Audit Row (Google Sheets)","width":280,"height":232,"color":7},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[4773,520],"id":"04524324-dab0-ec77-46c2-002024b8e673","name":"Note: Summarize Run Stats"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Append Audit Row (Google Sheets)\n\ngoogleSheets — `append` operation against the connected account.\n\nPorts: ①→ Send Summary to Slack · ②→ Capture Failure Context\n\n↻ retries 3×/2s · ⚠ failures exit via the error rail · 🔑 Google OAuth2 / service account","width":280,"height":232,"color":2},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[5097,520],"id":"b7789fb0-99f6-a674-3a42-bb8dad70d53a","name":"Note: Append Audit Row (Google Sheets)"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Send Summary to Slack\n\nslack — `action` operation against the connected account.\n\n↻ retries 3×/2s · ⚠ failures exit via the error rail · 🔑 Slack OAuth2","width":280,"height":232,"color":4},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[5421,520],"id":"ddc9cbfd-0b8c-4a49-cea9-67480fac92ea","name":"Note: Send Summary to Slack"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Capture Failure Context\n\nShapes the item: writes `failedNode`, `errorMessage`, `workflow`. Keeps the schema explicit between stages.\n\nNext: Escalate Failure to Telegram","width":280,"height":232,"color":3},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[4773,1540],"id":"e2d8e40d-3bff-6084-0a7f-1ef8e1f9be6c","name":"Note: Capture Failure Context"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Escalate Failure to Telegram\n\ntelegram — `action` operation against the connected account.\n\n↻ retries 3×/2s · 🔑 Telegram bot token","width":280,"height":232,"color":3},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[5097,1540],"id":"7c6fe795-7d68-169f-253e-6473aaf98d4d","name":"Note: Escalate Failure to Telegram"},{"parameters":{"content":"# Automate an AI agent task with Telegram for your team for Lead Bots\n\n**Pattern:** AI Agent · **Level:** Advanced · **Trigger:** Webhook\n\n## What it does\nAutomate an AI agent task with Telegram for your team for Lead Bots. It fires the moment an external system calls its webhook.\n\n## Why it exists\nManual lead bots is slow and error-prone; this workflow makes the process repeatable, monitored and hands-off, with failures surfaced instead of silently lost.\n\n## Main flow\nReceive Inbound Webhook → Collect Raw Text → Extract Structured Fields → All Required Fields Found? → Upsert into Google Sheets → Merge Review Paths → Sort Conversations Newest First → …\n\n## Use it for\n- Teams that want to ai agent without manual effort\n- Anyone automating lead bots in customer support\n- Replacing a fragile manual process with a reliable workflow\n\n## You get\n- Runs 24/7 in the background\n- Has retries and error handling built in\n- Responds in seconds\n\n## Before first run\nConnect credentials: Google OAuth2 / service account; OpenAI API key; Slack OAuth2; Telegram bot token.\nFollow the color key: 🟦 entry · 🟪 AI · 🟫 actions · ⬜ utilities · 🟩 outputs · 🟥 error rail.\nEach node has its own doc card underneath — read those before editing.","width":480,"height":900},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[-830,80],"id":"cdd8726f-a860-36ed-c973-4e756fd43347","name":"📘 Workflow Overview"},{"parameters":{"content":"## 🛟 Error handling & retries\n\nExternal calls retry **3× with 2s backoff**. Anything still failing exits through its node's error output into the red error rail → context is captured and the on-call channel is alerted. Set an n8n **Error Workflow** in settings as the final safety net.","width":360,"height":260,"color":3},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[-230,-260],"id":"b7452ca1-5606-35a0-ab8e-825549e5d642","name":"🛟 Error handling & retries"},{"parameters":{"content":"## 🔐 Security\n\nNever trust inbound payloads: the webhook path is unguessable. Add header auth or IP allow-listing for defense in depth. Secrets live in n8n credentials — never in node parameters.","width":360,"height":260,"color":1},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[190,-260],"id":"111f3a70-19ff-a719-f03f-f2444f2be88a","name":"🔐 Security"},{"parameters":{"content":"## 🤖 AI cluster\n\nPurple nodes form one AI unit: the root node orchestrates, sub-nodes plug in via typed ports (model / memory / tools / parser). Swap the chat model without rewiring anything else. Costs scale with tokens — keep prompts lean and cap iterations.","width":360,"height":260,"color":6},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[610,-260],"id":"5f9343b5-fcba-afa9-eeb8-b5cdf8ebccc5","name":"🤖 AI cluster"},{"parameters":{"content":"## 🛠 Customize me\n\nQuick wins: point the data nodes at your own accounts (see 🔑 lines on each card), adjust the trigger cadence, and tune thresholds/labels to your lead bots process. Every node card explains its role — safe to extend at any marked branch.","width":360,"height":260,"color":4},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[1030,-260],"id":"594f1653-1dfe-d514-6e10-638faf27cb24","name":"🛠 Customize me"}],"connections":{"Receive Inbound Webhook":{"main":[[{"node":"Collect Raw Text","type":"main","index":0}]]},"Collect Raw Text":{"main":[[{"node":"Extract Structured Fields","type":"main","index":0}]]},"OpenAI Chat Model":{"ai_languageModel":[[{"node":"Extract Structured Fields","type":"ai_languageModel","index":0}]]},"Extract Structured Fields":{"main":[[{"node":"All Required Fields Found?","type":"main","index":0}],[{"node":"Capture Failure Context","type":"main","index":0}]]},"All Required Fields Found?":{"main":[[{"node":"Upsert into Google Sheets","type":"main","index":0}],[{"node":"Queue for Manual Review","type":"main","index":0}]]},"Upsert into Google Sheets":{"main":[[{"node":"Merge Review Paths","type":"main","index":0}],[{"node":"Capture Failure Context","type":"main","index":0}]]},"Queue for Manual Review":{"main":[[{"node":"Merge Review Paths","type":"main","index":1}],[{"node":"Capture Failure Context","type":"main","index":0}]]},"Merge Review Paths":{"main":[[{"node":"Sort Conversations Newest First","type":"main","index":0}]]},"Sort Conversations Newest First":{"main":[[{"node":"Guard Non-Empty message","type":"main","index":0}]]},"Guard Non-Empty message":{"main":[[{"node":"Stamp Processing Time","type":"main","index":0}]]},"Stamp Processing Time":{"main":[[{"node":"Save Execution Metadata","type":"main","index":0}]]},"Save Execution Metadata":{"main":[[{"node":"Align Field Names","type":"main","index":0}]]},"Align Field Names":{"main":[[{"node":"Summarize Run Stats","type":"main","index":0}]]},"Summarize Run Stats":{"main":[[{"node":"Append Audit Row (Google Sheets)","type":"main","index":0}]]},"Append Audit Row (Google Sheets)":{"main":[[{"node":"Send Summary to Slack","type":"main","index":0}],[{"node":"Capture Failure Context","type":"main","index":0}]]},"Capture Failure Context":{"main":[[{"node":"Escalate Failure to Telegram","type":"main","index":0}]]},"Send Summary to Slack":{"main":[[],[{"node":"Capture Failure Context","type":"main","index":0}]]}},"active":false,"settings":{"executionOrder":"v1"},"meta":{"templateCredsSetupCompleted":false},"tags":[],"pinData":{},"versionId":"5ff7ab17-ecf4-4e1e-929a-b1b64fd27260","id":"FDX07640"}